ly news sources for relevant engineering content draft weekly posts for the school's social media channels facebook twitter g+ linkedin flickr picplz etc track record and report social media statistics keep us up to date on campus events relevant to engineering attend engineering related events when possible and capturing photos audio video to share via social media channels brainstorm new ways to engage current students and young alumni via social networks requirements excellent writing skills particularly short form must have a strong command of online search techniques and be tech savvy demonstrated interest in social media prior experience building an active following community with social media proficient in microsoft word excel and powerpoint must be very organized and efficient with excellent attention to detail should have a strong work ethic and a positive attitude and be comfortable working in a fast paced environment skills experience shooting editing photos and video are welcome extras please reply stanfordeng and tell us why you re perfect for the job include a link to your resume application deadline march 16 2012 last modified fri 2 mar 2012 at 13 54 staff media contacts andrew myers associate director of communications 650.736 2245 admyers stanford edu jamie beckett director of communications and alumni relations 650.736 2241 jbeckett stanford edu stay connected itunes icon google+ icon facebook icon twitter icon linkedin icon stanford university school of engineering 475 via ortega stanford california 94305 4121 650.725 1575 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved accreditation info terms of use copyright complaints contact us
